, then realized that I don't read that board and probably most other people don't... <br>
<br>
Did anything that was touched by this patch NOT get broken? Here's what I know<br>
so far. And one of my computers still will not run EQ at all now.<br>
<br>
1. The login screen was changed so that it can be in a windowed mode now. Suddenly hundreds if not thousands of people cannot load the login screen at all. EQ quits after hitting play on the patch screen.<br>
<br>
2. Charm was changed. Now there are reports of charmed pets and DC pets attacking players.<br>
<br>
3. FD is acting as a 100% aggro eraser. This has been announced at everquest.com as an error. Well, it was reported very widely by people playing on the test server at least a week or so ago and long threads were started on various message boards talking about the change and assuming that since it stayed in on test, it must be deliberate. A large portion of the active player base knew about the change before the patch. So being an error apparently, how the heck did it go Live?<br>
<br>
4. Aggro changes were made. Since then mages are reporting massively increased aggro from casting their spells, as our rangers with their bows, and rogues with their backstabbing. Along with other possible problems, it looks like possibly proximity aggro has disappeared. Being closer to a mob is having no effect on the aggro.  For anecdotal evidence, I did notice last night that the rogue in my group was getting aggro from me a LOT more often.  Something strange was definitely going on.<br>
<br>
5. Reports are coming in that people well out of melee range are getting hit for rampage damage. This has a huge impact on raiding. This may have something to do with #4 and the screwed up or maybe now nonexistent proximity aggro.<br>
<br>
6. Many mobs are no longer enraging. Okay, so that's a good thing for the players...  It's almost certainly a bug though.<br>
<br>
7. hmm... I've not heard any reports of bards being broken again yet. #7 is reserved for them though. <br>
<br>
Anything to add?<br>
<br>
This patch appears to have been coded by Verant's college interns.  It looks like nothing was tested as they broke almost everything they touched and something things that they supposedly weren't touching.  Things like FD being a 100% aggro erase on the test server were VERY widely known before the patch and yet somehow it went live anyway, so if they are testing stuff, they're ignoring the results.  Why is there a test server again?    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=brudal>Brudal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/03 12:11:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2059.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.championsinarms.com/hall/uploaded/brudal/Brusig.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The many patch bugs</span><hr size=1> Well I agree something is up with Agro. Last night on Emp Ssra, Creator and HP I had serious issues holding taunt and I usually don't loose agro on any of those fights.<br>
